John Zelepos of North Stonington faces up to 15 years in prison after pleading guilty Tuesday to tax evasion and financial structuring offenses .
Prosecutors said in a release that between 2006 and 2010, Zelepo diverted just over $567,000 from Mystic Pizza's gross receipts into his personal bank accounts and those of family members .
The restaurant owner may also be forced to pay a $500,000 fine .